clinical_study.brief_title: A Long-term Study for the Treatment of Painful Diabetic Neuropathy
clinical_study.official_title: A Superiority Study of LY248686 Versus Placebo in the Treatment of Patients With Diabetic Peripheral Neuropathic Pain - Extension Phase

brief_summary.textblock: The purpose of the study is to investigate safety and efficacy of duloxetine for patients with painful diabetic neuropathy at long-term use.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Participants Who Experienced an Adverse Event (AE)
primary_outcome.description: See the Reported Adverse Events section for details.

secondary_outcome.measure: Patient Global Impression of Improvement (PGI-I) Scale at One Year Endpoint.
secondary_outcome.description: A scale that measures the participant's perception of improvement at the time of assessment compared with the start of treatment. The score ranges from 1 (very much better) to 7 (very much worse).

secondary_outcome.measure: Change From Baseline to One Year Endpoint for Patient Global Impression of Improvement (PGI-I) Scale
secondary_outcome.description: A scale that measures the participant's perception of improvement at the time of assessment compared with the start of treatment. The score ranges from 1 (very much better) to 7 (very much worse).

secondary_outcome.measure: Brief Pain Inventory (BPI) Severity Scores at One Year Endpoint
secondary_outcome.description: A self-reported scale that measures the severity of pain. The severity scores range from 0 (no pain) to 10 (pain as severe as you can imagine). There are 4 questions assessing worst pain, least pain, and average pain in the past 24 hours, and the pain right now.

secondary_outcome.measure: Change From Baseline to One Year Endpoint in Brief Pain Inventory (BPI) Severity Scores
secondary_outcome.description: A self-reported scale that measures the severity of pain. The severity scores range from 0 (no pain) to 10 (pain as severe as you can imagine). There are 4 questions assessing worst pain, least pain, and average pain in the past 24 hours, and the pain right now.

secondary_outcome.measure: Brief Pain Inventory (BPI) Interference Scores at One Year Endpoint
secondary_outcome.description: Self-reported scale measures interference of pain on function in past 24 hours for general activity, mood, walking ability, normal work, relations with other people, sleep, enjoyment of life. Scores range from 0 (does not interfere) to 10 (completely interferes). Average interference = self-reported scale measures interference of pain on average of 7 questions assessing interference of pain for general activity, mood, walking ability, normal work, relations with other people, sleep, enjoyment of life. Average interference scores range from 0 (does not interfere) to 10 (completely interferes).

secondary_outcome.measure: Change From Baseline to One Year Endpoint in Brief Pain Inventory (BPI) Interference Scores
secondary_outcome.description: Self-reported scale measures interference of pain on function in past 24 hours for general activity, mood, walking ability, normal work, relations with other people, sleep, enjoyment of life. Scores range from 0 (does not interfere) to 10 (completely interferes). Average interference = self-reported scale measures interference of pain on average of 7 questions assessing interference of pain for general activity, mood, walking ability, normal work, relations with other people, sleep, enjoyment of life. Average interference scores range from 0 (does not interfere) to 10 (completely interferes).

secondary_outcome.measure: Beck Depression Inventory-II (BDI-II) Total Score at One Year Endpoint
secondary_outcome.description: A 21-item, participant-completed questionnaire to assess characteristics of depression. Each of the 21 items corresponding to a symptom of depression is summed to give a single score. There is a 4-point scale for each item ranging from 0 to 3. Total score of 0-13 is considered minimal range, 14-19 is mild, 20-28 is moderate, and 29-63 is severe.

Total score of 0-13 is considered minimal range, 14-19 is mild, 20-28 is moderate, and 29-63 is severe.

arm_group.description: Duloxetine 40 milligrams (mg) once daily (QD), orally (PO), 1 year

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Outpatients who have completed the 13-week treatment in the preceding study (Protocol No. 0715N0831: NCT00552175).
- Patients who desire to receive continued treatment with LY248686 from the preceding study.
- Patients with latest glycosylated hemoglobin (HbA1c) â‰¤9.0% before Visit 7.
- Patients who can provide written consent in person.
Exclusion Criteria:
- Patients who concurrently have serious cardiovascular, hepatic, renal, respiratory, or blood disease, or symptomatic peripheral vascular disease, and thus are considered inappropriate to be included in the study.
- Pregnant patients or women who desire to become pregnant during the study period, and breast feeding patients.
- Other patients judged by the investigator/subinvestigator to be inappropriate as a subject in this study.

participant_flow.recruitment_details: This study, F1J-JE-HMFY (Study HMFY), is an open-label, long-term extension study of double-blind placebo-controlled study F1J-JE-HMFX (Study HMFX) (NCT00552175).
participant_flow.pre_assignment_details: Prior to start of extension study (HMFY), all participants in Study HMFX were re-randomized to duloxetine 40 or 60 mg regardless of the treatment they received in Study HMFX. Baseline values for the extension study HMFY represent those of 40- and 60-mg groups after re-randomization of participants.

measure.title: Type of Diabetes
measure.description: Type I diabetes is insulin dependent diabetes. Type II diabetes is non-insulin dependent diabetes.

measure.title: Body Mass Index (BMI)
measure.description: Body mass index (BMI) is an estimate of body fat based on body weight divided by height squared (kg/m^2).

measure.title: Patient's Global Impressions of Improvement (PGI-I) Rate
measure.description: A scale that measures the participant's perception of improvement at the time of assessment compared with the start of treatment. The score ranges from 1 (very much better) to 7 (very much worse).

measure.title: Beck Depression Inventory - II (BDI-II)
measure.description: A 21-item, participant-completed questionnaire to assess characteristics of depression. Each of the 21 items corresponding to a symptom of depression is summed to give a single score. There is a 4-point scale for each item ranging from 0 to 3. Total score of 0-13 is considered minimal range, 14-19 is mild, 20-28 is moderate, and 29-63 is severe.

measure.title: Brief Pain Inventory (BPI) Interference
measure.description: Self-reported scale measures interference of pain on function in past 24 hours for general activity, mood, walking ability, normal work, relations with other people, sleep, enjoyment of life. Scores range from 0 (does not interfere) to 10 (completely interferes). Average interference = self-reported scale measures interference of pain on average of 7 questions assessing interference of pain for general activity, mood, walking ability, normal work, relations with other people, sleep, enjoyment of life. Average Interference scores range from 0 (does not interfere) to 10 (completely interferes).

measure.title: Brief Pain Inventory (BPI) - Pain Severity
measure.description: A self-reported scale that measures the severity of pain based on the average pain, least pain, and worst pain experienced over the past 24 hours, and the pain right now. The severity scores range from 0 (no pain) to 10 (pain as severe as you can imagine).
